<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
Ok, so as one of the main Mezzing classes for Hibernia, I'm sure many of you have already developed a deep dislike for Heroes (and others) breaking your mezzes. My question is: How can we help?<P>As a Hero, I tend to handle a lot of haphazard crowd control by Taunting everything onto me and praying that the healers are quick enough. This doesn't exactly work too well with a Mentalist in the group. So does this work for you?...<P>1. Hero Taunts everything onto him as it comes in.<BR>2. Once the Hero has everything busy, he concentrates on the primary mob with everyone else while the Mentalist mezzes away.<P>And what about when the mob breaks loose and runs after the Druid?<P>1. Hero Taunts the mob onto him and then stops attacking so it can be mezzed.<P>And the great nasty, the mob runs after YOU, the Mentalist.<P>1. Hero hauls arse to your side and Taunts until you are being ignored. You now have a chance to remezz.<P>These are some of the scenarios I've seen as a Hero and they almost never work out quite this way either because the Mentalist gives up (can't blame him) or I give up and just keep attacking because the Mentalist gave up earlier. I look forward to your input on this subject.<P>--------------------<P>Happy! Happy! Bash! Bash!
</FONT>
