<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
I rarely get to use mez because the tank does exactly what you said - switches targets constantly and taunting. If i ever did have a chance to mez however, i would prefer that the tank (and any other people doing melee... use /assist!!) stayed on 1 mob and allowed the Ment to take care of the others. If it breaks mez and goes for the druid, the Ment can have it mezzed again in a few seconds. If it comes for the Ment, we have quickcast... it may make the spell cost more mana, but you can't be interupted. As long as the mez isn't resisted, the Ment is fine. Of course if the mez is resisted, or the moib breaks mez before the tank is done with the other mob, then the Ment is in trouble  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0">
</FONT>
